True Freedom: Leaving the Stage Behind

December 31, 2024

For most of my life, I thought I was living a real life. A life grounded in truth, purpose, and reality. But over time, I began to notice something unsettling: the world is filled with actors playing their parts in a grand system designed to keep us asleep. Talk shows, news anchors, entertainers, and even many of us in our day-to-day roles. They are all part of a practice that feeds us information and dictates how we should walk, talk, and think.

The deeper I looked, the more obvious it became: this is not true life.

Most careers, roles, and identities are rehearsed practices, not genuine expressions of self. We are taught to follow scripts written by someone else, rarely pausing to question the authenticity of what we are doing or why we are doing it. The system thrives on conformity, on us playing our parts without ever asking when it is time to stop practicing and start truly creating. Not just for survival, but for the higher purpose we all came here to fulfill.

A World Divided

The world we live in is fragmented, divided in so many ways that it is hard to know what deserves our attention. Social issues, political narratives, technological distractions. It is overwhelming, and it was never supposed to be this way.

We were born whole, connected to a deeper truth, and yet we have become disconnected. Why? Because we live in a system where questioning what is true has been replaced by blind obedience. We have forgotten who we are and the power we hold.

It’s time to come back online.

The Shift Is Here

We are at a pivotal moment in human history, a time of great transition. You have two choices:

  1. Stay in the comfort of the known, repeating the same patterns, stagnant and tied to survival
  2. Embrace the unknown, confront your fears, and unlock the vast potential of your existence

Neither choice is inherently wrong, but the second choice is the path of creation, the path that moves you beyond the 3D world of materialism and survival into something far greater.

Many of us live instinctively, like animals focused solely on survival. Yet, we are meant for so much more. This experience we call life is a playground of potential, a canvas of infinite possibilities. But tapping into that potential requires breaking free from the system and stepping into a new way of being.

The Illusion of Time

There is another layer to this shift: time itself.

The Gregorian calendar, the system we use to mark days and years, was introduced to create structure and order. But in doing so, it also altered our perception of time, disconnecting us from natural cycles and rhythms. What if this system is not as accurate as we think? What if what has been written about for centuries is unfolding now, faster than we anticipated?

Many people sense that something significant is happening. The illusions are beginning to crumble, and the truth is becoming harder to ignore.

What If the World Was Ending?

Ask yourself this: if the world as we know it were coming to an end, what would you do?

Would you cling to the familiar, hoping for a return to normalcy? Or would you say, “Enough is enough,” and make the changes necessary to give yourself a fighting chance. Not just to survive, but to thrive?

Most people will ignore this call. They will continue playing their roles, content in the safety of their scripts. But you do not have to.

The Call to Action

This is your wake-up call. It is an opportunity to step into the life you were always meant to live. A life of authenticity, creation, and connection to your true self.

  • Question the system. Ask yourself why you believe what you believe and whether it serves your highest good.
  • Challenge your routines. Break free from the patterns that keep you stagnant and start exploring the unknown.
  • Reconnect with your purpose. Remember the knowledge, gifts, and keys you came here with, and use them to create a new reality.

We are shifting into a time where the veil is lifting, and clarity is available to those who seek it. The scripts, the actors, the distractions. They no longer hold the power they once did. This is your moment to reclaim your life, to live not as a character in someone else’s story, but as the creator of your own.

Will you answer the call? Or will you continue to play your part in the old system, letting life pass you by?

The choice is yours.

But remember, you were made for more. 

THE TIME IS NOW!


hunter johnson
